Description: Neck and shoulder sherd (mended from three fragments) of East Greek (North Ionian) Late Wild Goat (black-figured) pottery oinochoe or amphora; pale orange clay with white inclusions and some silver mica; cream slip, part of a sphinx and a goose in an antithetical composition; filling ornaments: rosettes, pendant half-rosettes; at top of shoulder frieze of degenerate tongues; ridge at base of neck; above, part of a floral ornament(?); red patches on hair of sphinx and on neck and wing of goose; incision used for part of the outline and for details of sphinx and of goose.
Curator's comments: For parallels (swan confronting siren), see Cambridge NA22.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GG.662)
